      "wikitext": "{{Infobox mineral\n|name        = Prismatic Shard\n|image       = Prismatic Shard.png\n|source      = \n[[Mining]] • [[Fishing#Treasure Chests|Fishing Treasure Chests]] • [[Monsters]]' drop • [[Omni Geode|Omni Geodes]] • [[Rainbow Trout]] [[Fish Pond]]s • [[Skull Cavern#Treasure Rooms|Treasure room]] • [[Statue Of True Perfection]] • [[Random Events#Meteorite|Meteorite]] • [[Mystery Box]] • [[Golden Mystery Box]]\n|sellprice   = 2000\n|profession  = y\n}}\nThe '''Prismatic Shard''' is a [[Minerals|Mineral]]. It is one of the rarest items in the game, and has a variety of uses, including obtaining the [[Galaxy Sword]].\n\n==Locations==\nPrismatic shards can be found in:\n* 25% chance from a [[Mining#Mystic Stone|Mystic Stone]] in [[the Mines]] at floors 100+, [[Skull Cavern]], and [[Quarry]].\n* 25% chance from a [[Random Events#Meteorite|meteorite]].\n* 1/26 (≈3.8%) chance from a [[Skull Cavern#Treasure Rooms|treasure room]] in the Skull Cavern.\n* 3.5% chance from an [[Mining#Iridium Node|Iridium Node]] in the [[Skull Cavern]], [[Quarry]] and [[Volcano Dungeon]].\n* 0.4% chance from an [[Omni Geode]].\n* 0.4% chance from a [[Mystery Box]].<!--please add % chance when known-->\n* 0.1% chance from [[Serpent]]s and [[Mummy|Mummies]] (and their dangerous variants). 0.05% chance from [[Shadow Brute]]s and [[Shadow Shaman]] (and their dangerous variants). \n* 0.1% chance from [[Wilderness Golem]]s and [[Iridium Golem]]s after reaching [[Combat]] Level 10.\n* 0.79% chance from a [[Golden Mystery Box]].\n* 0.09% daily chance from a [[Rainbow Trout]] [[Fish Pond]] with a population of at least 9.\n* 0.05% chance from any [[Monsters|monster]] after the player has reached the bottom of [[the Mines]].  \n* ≈0.012% chance from a [[Fishing#Treasure Chests|Fishing Treasure Chest]] after reaching [[Fishing#Fishing Skill|fishing level 6]].\n* One in a chest at the top of the [[Volcano Dungeon]] the first time the player arrives there.\n* Once per day from the [[Statue Of True Perfection]].\n* Purchased from [[Emily]] for {{Price|500|Calico}} [[Calico Egg]]s when she hosts a [[Desert Festival#Villager Shop|shop]] during the [[Desert Festival]].\n* From the [[Statue Of Blessings#List of Blessings|Blessing Of The Butterfly]] (up to a 17.5% chance).\n\n==Uses==\n* A Prismatic Shard can be used in [[the Desert]] to obtain the [[Galaxy Sword]]. The [[Graveyard#Dwarvish Headstone|Dwarvish Headstone]] in the graveyard contains a riddle explaining how to obtain it.\n* A Prismatic Shard is one of the options used to complete [[Bundles#The Missing Bundle|the Missing Bundle]] to unlock the [[Movie Theater]].\n* A Prismatic Shard can be offered to the [[Dark Shrine of Selfishness]] at the [[Witch's Hut]] to turn [[children]] into doves (getting rid of them permanently).\n* On [[Days of the Week#Thursday|Thursdays]] the [[Desert Trader]] sells 1 [[Magic Rock Candy]] for 3 Prismatic Shards.\n* Prismatic Shards are used to enchant tools in the [[Forge]].\n* A Prismatic Shard can be placed into a [[Junimo Hut]] to cause the [[Junimos|Junimo]] to cycle through the rainbow resembling a Prismatic Shard.\n* A Prismatic Shard can be donated to [[Gunther]] at the [[Museum]].\n* A Prismatic Shard can be used in the [[Sewing Machine]] to create prismatic clothing (see [[#Tailoring|Tailoring]] below).\n* Prismatic Shards can be [[Friendship#Gifts|gifted]] as a universally loved gift (to everyone except [[Haley]]).\n*[[Multiplayer]] only: A Prismatic Shard can be used to craft a [[Wedding Ring]] to propose marriage to another player.\n\n==Gifting==\n{{GiftsByItem\n|love=Robin,Demetrius,Maru,Sebastian,Linus,Pierre,Caroline,Abigail,Alex,George,Evelyn,Lewis,Clint,Penny,Pam,Emily,Jas,Vincent,Jodi,Kent,Sam,Leah,Shane,Marnie,Elliott,Gus,Dwarf,Wizard,Harvey,Sandy,Willy,Krobus,Leo\n|hate=Haley\n}}\n\n==Bundles==\nOne Prismatic Shard is an option for {{Bundle|Missing||y}}.\n\n==Recipes==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n!Image\n!Name\n!Description\n!Ingredients\n!Recipe Source\n|-\n|[[File:Wedding Ring.png|center]]\n|[[Wedding Ring]]\n|{{Description|Wedding Ring}}<p>''Used only in [[multiplayer]] games.''</p>\n|{{Name|Iridium Bar|5}}{{Name|Prismatic Shard|1}}\n|[[Traveling Cart]] {{Price|500}}\n|}\n\n==Tailoring==\nPrismatic Shard is used in the spool of a [[Sewing Machine]] to create one of 5 random \"prismatic\" [[Tailoring|clothing items]]. It is possible to obtain duplicates before obtaining all 5 items.\n*[[File:Shirt223.png|24px]] Prismatic Shirt\n*[[File:Shirt288a.png|24px]] Prismatic Shirt (white sleeves)\n*[[File:Shirt289a.png|24px]] Prismatic Shirt (black sleeves)\n*[[File:Farmer Pants.png|24px]] Prismatic Pants\n*[[File:Genie Pants.png|24px]] Prismatic Genie Pants\n\n==Quests==\n4 Prismatic Shards are requested in [[Mr. Qi]]'s [[Quests#Four Precious Stones|Four Precious Stones]] quest.\n\n==Notes==\n*Prismatic Shards cannot be duplicated in a [[Crystalarium]]. According to the Lost Book ''[[Lost Books#Technology Report!|Technology Report!]]'', \"the EMF from the shard interacts negatively with the crystalarium.\"\n\n==History==\n{{History|1.0|Introduced.}}\n{{History|1.3.27|Added to all monster drop pools after player has reached the bottom of [[the Mines]].}}\n{{History|1.4|Added as option for [[Bundles#Abandoned JojaMart|Missing Bundle]]. Fixed bug where an entire stack would be consumed when obtaining the [[Galaxy Sword]]. Can now be used in [[Tailoring]]. Can be produced by [[Fish Pond]]s.}}\n{{History|1.5|Can be used to [[Forge#Enchantments|enchant tools]]. Obtained from the [[Statue Of True Perfection]]. One can be obtained at the top of the [[Volcano Dungeon]]. Requested in [[Quests#Four Precious Stones|Four Precious Stones]].}}\n{{History|1.6|Chance of obtaining Prismatic Shard from [[Mining#Iridium Node|Iridium Node]] decreased from 4% to 3.5%. Can now be obtained from [[Mystery Box]], [[Golden Mystery Box]],  [[Random Events#Meteorite|Meteorite]], and [[Iridium Golem]]. Can now be purchased from [[Emily]] at the [[Desert Festival]].}}\n{{History|1.6.3|Reduced rate of the [[Random Events#Meteorite|Meteorite]] dropping a Prismatic Shard from 100% to 25%.}}\n\n{{NavboxMinerals}}\n\n[[Category:Gems]]\n\n[[de:Prismatische Scherbe]]\n[[es:Esquirla prismática]]\n[[fr:Tesson prismatique]]\n[[it:Scheggia prismatica]]\n[[ja:レインボージェム]]\n[[ko:무지갯빛 파편]]\n[[hu:Prizmás töredék]]\n[[pt:Fragmento prismático]]\n[[ru:Радужный осколок]]\n[[tr:Prizma Parçası]]\n[[zh:五彩碎片]]"
    }
